  "text": "In Australia, frameworks for professional education and accreditation, combined with significant international higher education markets in the Middle East and South-East Asia, produce diversity in undergraduate nursing cohorts. Some students are school-leavers with no prior clinical experience, while others may have several years' experience in clinical positions for which tertiary qualifications were not required. Layered onto these differences are variations in the cultural location of prior experience: international students often find features of the Australian healthcare and educational systems unfamiliar and daunting [CITATION_1] . Thus, educators in our Australian example view diversity as a key concern related to difficulty.",
